Preheat the oven to 200C/400F/Gas 6.For the sausage, rub the sausage with the oil and place on a small baking tray. Place into the oven and roast for 15-20 minutes, or until completely cooked through.To make the mash, place the cooked potato and swede into a bowl and mash with a potato masher or a ricer.Add the butter, garlic and cream, season well with salt and freshly ground black pepper and stir to mix.To serve, place the mash in the centre of a warm plate with the roasted Cumberland sausage on top.